The paper deals with instance retrieval using convolutional feature maps, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also proposes a novel reranking algorithm, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on several benchmarks, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
